  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 but H4 CSM has faded to 44, a 56-point divergence flagged as the most critical short-term signal in this brief, while CHF H4 CSM has surged to 100 versus D1 at 33 and AUD H4 CSM sits at 70 versus D1 at 31, both indicating intraday strength rotating away from USD. USDCHF is the highest-conviction expression given the EURUSD-USDCHF -0.90 correlation locking CHF strength across the board, while AUDUSD and AUDJPY both align via their +0.90 correlation cluster amplifying the AUD H4 acceleration. Bond vigilante concerns with US 10Y at 4.558 down 0.61% compressing the yield curve represent a structural headwind for USD that validates the H4 fade.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: None\n\nWATCH\nUSDCAD D1 Strong Buy H4 Buy confluence breaks above recent range, CAD weakness via CADJPY H4 sell at -4 confirms CAD as funding leg, triggering further USDCAD extension higher.\nUS 10Y yield reversal above 4.60 hits USDJPY directly given CADJPY +0.67 correlation, pushing USDJPY and CADJPY bid simultaneously.\nCopper sustaining above 6.38 accelerates AUD H4 momentum, making AUDJPY the cleanest long given AUDUSD-AUDJPY +0.90 correlation amplification.",
